  "text": "Since M. smegmatis and M. goodii have similar 16S rDNA sequences, isolates belonging or closely related to these two species were differentiated by single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) analysis of their 16S rDNA sequences (Figure 1 ; [CITATION_1] . Alignment of part of the isolate's 16S rDNA as well as that of M. goodii and M. smegmatis reference sequences extracted from NCBI Nucleotide (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ nuccore) database was also performed using MEGA version 7. SNP identification was done manually.",
