    "24918632": {
      "title": "Pulmonary infection due to Mycobacterium goodii in a spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta) from South Africa",
      "abstract": "We report a case of pyogranulomatous pneumonia due to infection with Mycobacterium goodii in an adult female spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta). The lungs of the animal showed consolidated, granulomatous lesions, and they were extensively and severely infiltrated. Polymerase chain reaction sequencing of isolated crude lung tissue DNA, and boiled lung culture samples, all confirmed that the causative organism was M. goodii, a recently described fast-growing organism closely related to the nonpathogenic mycobac-terial species M. smegmatis. The current study illustrates that this organism can be pathogenic and cause extensive pulmonary disease."
